JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 1175
EP  - 1218
VL  - 85
IS  - 4
KW  - Pure altruism
KW  - nonpaternalistic altruism
KW  - time inconsistency
KW  - present bias
KW  - intergenerational welfare
KW  - quasi-hyperbolic discounting
KW  - welfare criterion
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA13937
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Modeling intergenerational altruism is crucial to evaluate the long-term consequences of current decisions, and requires a set of principles guiding such altruism. We axiomatically develop a theory of pure, direct altruism: Altruism is pure if it concerns the total utility (rather than the mere consumption utility) of future generations, and direct if it directly incorporates the utility of all future generations. Our axioms deliver a new class of altruistic, forward-looking preferences, whose weight put on the consumption of a future generation generally depends on the consumption of other generations. The only preferences lacking this dependence correspond to the quasi-hyperbolic discounting model, which our theory characterizes. Our approach provides a framework to analyze welfare in the presence of altruistic preferences and addresses technical challenges stemming from the interdependent nature of such preferences.
ER  - 

